{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.31",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 31 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:1",
      "text": "The words of King Lemuel — the revelation which his mother taught him:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:2",
      "text": "“Oh, my son! Oh, son of my womb! Oh, son of my vows!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:3",
      "text": "Don’t give your strength to women, nor your ways to that which destroys kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:4",
      "text": "It is not for kings, Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine, nor for princes to say, ‘Where is strong drink?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:5",
      "text": "lest they drink, and forget the law, and pervert the justice due to anyone who is afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:6",
      "text": "Give strong drink to him who is ready to perish, and wine to the bitter in soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:7",
      "text": "Let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:8",
      "text": "Open your mouth for the mute, in the cause of all who are left desolate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:9",
      "text": "Open your mouth, judge righteously, and serve justice to the poor and needy.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:10",
      "text": "Who can find a worthy woman? For her value is far above rubies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:11",
      "text": "The heart of her husband trusts in her. He shall have no lack of gain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:12",
      "text": "She does him good, and not harm, all the days of her life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:13",
      "text": "She seeks wool and flax, and works eagerly with her hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:14",
      "text": "She is like the merchant ships. She brings her bread from afar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:15",
      "text": "She rises also while it is yet night, gives food to her household, and portions for her servant girls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:16",
      "text": "She considers a field, and buys it. With the fruit of her hands, she plants a vineyard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:17",
      "text": "She arms her waist with strength, and makes her arms strong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:18",
      "text": "She perceives that her merchandise is profitable. Her lamp doesn’t go out by night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:19",
      "text": "She lays her hands to the distaff, and her hands hold the spindle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:20",
      "text": "She opens her arms to the poor; yes, she extends her hands to the needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:21",
      "text": "She is not afraid of the snow for her household, for all her household are clothed with scarlet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:22",
      "text": "She makes for herself carpets of tapestry. Her clothing is fine linen and purple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:23",
      "text": "Her husband is respected in the gates, when he sits among the elders of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:24",
      "text": "She makes linen garments and sells them, and delivers sashes to the merchant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:25",
      "text": "Strength and dignity are her clothing. She laughs at the time to come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:26",
      "text": "She opens her mouth with wisdom. Kind instruction is on her tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:27",
      "text": "She looks well to the ways of her household, and doesn’t eat the bread of idleness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:28",
      "text": "Her children rise up and call her blessed. Her husband also praises her:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:29",
      "text": "“ Many women do noble things, but you excel them all.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:30",
      "text": "Charm is deceitful, and beauty is vain; but a woman who fears Yahweh, she shall be praised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.31.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:31",
      "text": "Give her of the fruit of her hands! Let her works praise her in the gates!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
